    • Method Detail

      • activeElement

        public static GetActiveElementSupplier activeElement​()
        Builds a function which performs the switching to the active element and returns it. Taken from Selenium documentation:

        Switches to the element that currently has focus within the document currently "switched to", or the body element if this cannot be detected. This matches the semantics of calling "document.activeElement" in Javascript. Returns the WebElement with focus, or the body element if no element with focus can be detected.

        Returns:
        an instance of GetActiveElementSupplier which wraps a function. This function performs the switching to the active element and returns it.

      • activeElement

        public static GetActiveElementSupplier activeElement​(java.time.Duration duration)
        Builds a function which performs the switching to the active element and returns it. Taken from Selenium documentation:

        Switches to the element that currently has focus within the document currently "switched to", or the body element if this cannot be detected. This matches the semantics of calling "document.activeElement" in Javascript. Returns the WebElement with focus, or the body element if no element with focus can be detected.

        Parameters:
        duration - is the time value to get the result which differs from null
        Returns:
        an instance of GetActiveElementSupplier which wraps a function. This function performs the switching to the active element and returns it.
